al</Type><Text>The hotel located in Samui Island, where guests can go either by a plane or by boat from mainland. The hotel is at south of Samui and can be reached by taking the highway 4170. After passing the Wat Kiriwonkaram guests should continue the drive until they see the hotel on the right-hand side.</Text></Description><Description><Language>en</Language><Type>DiningFacilities</Type><Text>Drawing inspiration from Thailand, Morocco and Bali, this bungalow complex, built in 2008, offers sanctuary within an eclectic blend of colour, texture, ancient healing wisdom and ecological environment providing a tantalising blend of sources of well-being and pleasure. Both communal and private spaces are offered among the tropical gardens and walking paths and of course the activities on the seaside below. The resort comprises a lobby with 24-hour reception, 18 bungalow units, 3 deluxe rooms and 2 junior suites. A safe is available to guests. A bar and restaurant cater to guests' dining and refreshments, whilst a laundry service, car park and bicycle hire are on offer for guests' convenience.</Text></Description><Amenity><Code>Safe</Code><Text>Safe</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>TVInRoom</Code><Text>TV in room</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>OutdoorPool</Code><Text>Outdoor swimming pool</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>MiniBarInRoom</Code><Text>Mini-bar</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>RoomService</Code><Text>Room service</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>Bar</Code><Text>Bar</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>LaundryService</Code><Text>Laundry service</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>CarPark</Code><Text>Car parking</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>ReceptionArea</Code><Text>Reception Area</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>Reception24hr</Code><Text>24hr. Reception</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>MobilePhoneNetwork</Code><Text>Mobile Phone Network</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>WLANAccessPoint</Code><Text>WLAN Access Point</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>BicycleRental</Code><Text>Bicycle Rental